  m_Name: DialogNPCShoreClues
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  Name: Recent Supply Transfers between St.Elmo and St.Angelo
  Icon: {fileID: 21300196, guid: 7810966f0f690954c87305933cabf2b0, type: 3}
  HasInteraction: 0
  interactionType: 3
  Greeting: MARTO 11 LABS
  Day1Dialog:
  - "Near the harbour path, you find a broken crate marked for artillery use. Several
    iron shot are missing, taken recently. The wood is still splintered, as if it
    was dropped in haste. Someone was moving ammunition through here not long ago\u2014and
    did not have time to clean up."
  Day2FirstTimeDialog:
  - Behind a low wall, scraps of food remain wrapped in cloth. The bread is stale
    but not spoiled. The bundle looks prepared for transport rather than storage.
    Supplies were packed and moved recently, likely under cover of darkness.
  Day2MetBeforeDialog:
  - Behind a low wall, scraps of food remain wrapped in cloth. The bread is stale
    but not spoiled. The bundle looks prepared for transport rather than storage.
    Supplies were packed and moved recently, likely under cover of darkness.
  Day3FirstTimeDialog:
  - You notice blood on the stones near the waterline, thin and smeared rather than
    pooled. A strip of bandage lies discarded nearby. Someone wounded was brought
    through here, carried rather than walking. The trail ends abruptly at the harbour.
  Day3MetBeforeDialog:
  - You notice blood on the stones near the waterline, thin and smeared rather than
    pooled. A strip of bandage lies discarded nearby. Someone wounded was brought
    through here, carried rather than walking. The trail ends abruptly at the harbour.
  Day4FirstTimeDialog:
  - "A helmet and shield lean against a crate, neither properly stored nor discarded.
    They are clean\u2014unused\u2014but the straps are freshly adjusted. Equipment
    like this would only be left behind if its owner moved on quickly. More men were
    sent forward."
  Day4MetBeforeDialog:
  - "A helmet and shield lean against a crate, neither properly stored nor discarded.
    They are clean\u2014unused\u2014but the straps are freshly adjusted. Equipment
    like this would only be left behind if its owner moved on quickly. More men were
    sent forward."
  Day5FirstTimeDialog:
  - "Today, there is less to find. Crates are stacked but lighter than they should
    be. The markings remain, but the contents are gone. Whatever passed through here
    recently took almost everything with it. The supply line is still active\u2014but
    strained."
  Day5MetBeforeDialog:
  - "Today, there is less to find. Crates are stacked but lighter than they should
    be. The markings remain, but the contents are gone. Whatever passed through here
    recently took almost everything with it. The supply line is still active\u2014but
    strained."
